  "title": "TCM Physician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Completion of a three-to four-year diploma or degree program in traditional Chinese medicine and acupuncture from recognized medical schools;</li>\n  <li>Experience in orthopaedics is a valued asset;</li>\n  <li>Experience in treating pain using cupping and herbs is an asset;</li>\n  <li>Have enthusiasm and possess excellent customer service skills and are able to build long-term relationships with customers;</li>\n  <li>Be able to effectively work and communicate with other practitioners in a team environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Meet with patients to obtain information about their complaints, symptoms, medical history, diet, lifestyle, and psychological health in order to diagnose diseases, physiological disorders or injuries;</li>\n  <li>Develop a treatment plan based on the diagnosis and explain procedures to patients and prepare them for treatment;</li>\n  <li>Provide professional traditional services and treatments;</li>\n  <li>Comply with quality, safety, and infection prevention protocols, as well as laws and regulations;</li>\n  <li>Maintain a positive attitude and contribute toward a quality work environment.</li>\n</ul>",
